HEADWORD: Creviced
<hw>Crev"iced</hw> <pr>(-?st)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having a crevice
or crevices; <as>as, a <ex>creviced</ex> structure for storing ears of
corn</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Trickling through the <qex>creviced</qex> rock.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Cunningham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crevis</ent>⟦br⟧
